    "value": "Pleiades-Neo is a four-satellite very high resolution Earth observation constellation operated by Airbus Defence and Space, designed as a follow-on to the Pleiades-HR satellites. The satellites carry an imager with 30 cm ground resolution and use a 700 km orbit with two orbital planes to allow intra-day revisit times. They use TesatSpacecom laser communication relay terminals to transfer data via the EDRS network, enabling near real time access to imagery.",
